-- Schroders appoints Peter Harrison to board as head of investment
-- By Jemima Kelly
-- Wed May 21, 2014 06:58AM EDT
-- None



LONDON, May 21 (Reuters) - British fund manager Schroders <SDR.L> has appointed Peter Harrison, previously the firm's global head of equities, to the board as head of investment, the company said on Wednesday.

The FTSE 100 firm said the appointment of Harrison, who began his career at Schroders in 1988 and went on to hold senior positions at other firms including JPMorgan <JPM.N> and Deutsche Asset Management, would take effect immediately.